</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-512_"><strong>Speak up. </strong>Use your voice on social media to raise awareness about fashion justice.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-514_"><strong>Buy less—but better. </strong>Choose timeless pieces made with respect.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bkSTSn iEaWBl pf-517_"><strong>Ask questions.</strong> When in doubt, ask who made your clothes—and under what conditions.
</li></ul><p class="sc-dQEsWe kFLVLU pf-188_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fFlofg cnCjdX pf-190_"> <strong>Fair trade isn’t about perfection. It’s about intention. </strong>About building a culture of responsibility and refusing to normalize exploitation.



 












 










<strong><br>

</strong></span></p><img alt="artisan-hands-pottery-slow-fashion-fair-trade.webp__PID:ca6145c3-84a9-4ff3-aa16-abe8f6867233" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/artisan-hands-pottery-slow-fashion-fair-trade.webp?v=1746829814&width=2048" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/artisan-hands-pottery-slow-fashion-fair-trade.webp?v=1746829814&width=375 375w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/artisan-hands-pottery-slow-fashion-fair-trade.webp?v=1746829814&width=550 550w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/artisan-hands-pottery-slow-fashion-fair-trade.webp?v=1746829814&width=768 768w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/artisan-hands-pottery-slow-fashion-fair-trade.webp?v=1746829814&width=1024 1024w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/artisan-hands-pottery-slow-fashion-fair-trade.webp?v=1746829814&width=1280 1280w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/artisan-hands-pottery-slow-fashion-fair-trade.webp?v=1746829814&width=1440 1440w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/artisan-hands-pottery-slow-fashion-fair-trade.webp?v=1746829814&width=1680 1680w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/artisan-hands-pottery-slow-fashion-fair-trade.webp?v=1746829814&width=1800 1800w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/artisan-hands-pottery-slow-fashion-fair-trade.webp?v=1746829814&width=1920 1920w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/artisan-hands-pottery-slow-fashion-fair-trade.webp?v=1746829814&width=2048 2048w" fetchPriority="low" decoding="async" loading="lazy" style="--pf-image-ratio:1.6" width="1280" height="800" sizes="75vw" data-pf-type="Image4" class="sc-kMriOJ jsCfBi pf-197_" store="[object Object]"/><p class="sc-dQEsWe kFLVLU pf-529_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fFlofg cnCjdX pf-528_"><strong><a href="https://nopr.niscpr.res.in/bitstream/123456789/24664/1/IJFTR%2029%284%29%20483-492.pdf" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"></span></a></strong><a href="https://www.statista.com/topics/9288/fashion-e-commerce-worldwide/" target="_blank"></a><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"></span><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);">Fashion worker handling harmful dyes without the necessary protection.</span><br>

</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cVzzKN eMDdXJ pf-198_ pf-heading-1-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fFlofg cnCjdX pf-200_"> Final Reflection






















</span></h2><p class="sc-dQEsWe kFLVLU pf-201_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fFlofg cnCjdX pf-203_"><strong><a href="https://nopr.niscpr.res.in/bitstream/123456789/24664/1/IJFTR%2029%284%29%20483-492.pdf" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"></span></a></strong><a href="https://www.statista.com/topics/9288/fashion-e-commerce-worldwide/" target="_blank"></a><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"></span><em>If fashion is about expressing who we are, then what does it say when our clothes are built on injustice?</em>
 

<br>

</span></p><p class="sc-dQEsWe kFLVLU pf-204_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fFlofg cnCjdX pf-206_">We live in a world of contradiction. A world where a t-shirt costs very little money, and we don't consider the environmental cost, stolen wages, and invisible lives. But Fair Trade World Day reminds us that change is possible—and urgently necessary.
 
 

<br>

</span></p><p class="sc-dQEsWe kFLVLU pf-520_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fFlofg cnCjdX pf-519_">At <strong><a href="https://www.ecoaya.com/" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);">AYA</span></a></strong>, we believe clothing is a statement. Not just of style, but of values. We design every collection with care, traceability, and respect. Because we are not just in fashion—we are in community. In resistance. In global consciousness.

 
 

<br>

</span></p><p class="sc-dQEsWe kFLVLU pf-523_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fFlofg cnCjdX pf-522_">This Fair Trade Day, let’s remember: <strong>fashion isn’t neutral</strong>. It can either uphold inequality or dismantle it.


 
 

<br>

</span></p><p class="sc-dQEsWe kFLVLU pf-207_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fFlofg cnCjdX pf-209_"><strong><a href="https://nopr.niscpr.res.in/bitstream/123456789/24664/1/IJFTR%2029%284%29%20483-492.pdf" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"></span></a></strong><a href="https://www.statista.com/topics/9288/fashion-e-commerce-worldwide/" target="_blank"></a><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"></span><strong>We choose to dismantle it.
</strong><br>

</span></p><img alt="fair_trade_cotton_fields_peru.webp__PID:67b488ff-9367-4264-b791-78d8f64eab9a" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/fair_trade_cotton_fields_peru.webp?v=1746829696&width=2048" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/fair_trade_cotton_fields_peru.webp?v=1746829696&width=375 375w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/fair_trade_cotton_fields_peru.webp?v=1746829696&width=550 550w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/fair_trade_cotton_fields_peru.webp?v=1746829696&width=768 768w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/fair_trade_cotton_fields_peru.webp?v=1746829696&width=1024 1024w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/fair_trade_cotton_fields_peru.webp?v=1746829696&width=1280 1280w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/fair_trade_cotton_fields_peru.webp?v=1746829696&width=1440 1440w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/fair_trade_cotton_fields_peru.webp?v=1746829696&width=1680 1680w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/fair_trade_cotton_fields_peru.webp?v=1746829696&width=1800 1800w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/fair_trade_cotton_fields_peru.webp?v=1746829696&width=1920 1920w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/files/fair_trade_cotton_fields_peru.webp?v=1746829696&width=2048 2048w" fetchPriority="low" decoding="async" loading="lazy" style="--pf-image-ratio:1.7772511848341233" width="6000" height="3376" sizes="75vw" data-pf-type="Image4" class="sc-kMriOJ jsCfBi pf-210_" store="[object Object]"/></div></div><div class="pf-c pf-sm-hide pf-hide" style="--c-xs:3;--c-sm:2;--c-md:6;--c-lg:3"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fsvrPk ezIRGP pf-211_ pf-sm-hide pf-hide"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-212_ pf-heading-1-h3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><strong>Glossary<span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.23);">keywords</span></strong><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.23);"></span><span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.23);"></span></span></h3><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-214_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Artisan:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">A skilled craftsperson who makes products by hand, often using traditional methods passed down through generations.



</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-216_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Climate justice:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">A term that links human rights and development to climate action, emphasizing that those least responsible for climate change often suffer its worst consequences.

   



</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-218_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Dignity:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">The state of being worthy of respect. In fashion, it refers to treating workers as valuable human beings, not disposable labor.
</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-220_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Exploitation:  </strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);"> The unfair treatment or use of someone for personal gain, especially by paying them unfairly or subjecting them to unsafe conditions.









</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-222_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Fair trade:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">A global movement and certification system that promotes ethical, transparent, and sustainable business practices for producers and workers.



</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-224_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Fast fashion:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">A business model that produces cheap, trendy clothing at high speed, often relying on exploitative labor and environmentally harmful practices.

   



</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-226_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Living wage:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">A salary that covers the basic needs of a worker and their family, including housing, food, education, and healthcare.

   



</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-228_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Overproduction:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">The excessive manufacture of goods beyond demand, common in fast fashion, leading to waste and environmental damage.

   



</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-230_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Slow fashion:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">A movement that promotes mindful, sustainable, and ethical production and consumption of clothing, focusing on quality over quantity.

   



</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-232_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Transparency:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">The practice of openly sharing information about sourcing, production, and labor conditions to allow accountability and informed decisions.

   



</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-236_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fsvrPk ezIRGP pf-237_"><div data-pf-type="Divider2" class="sc-dkmVhU NzRKb pf-238_ pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide"><span data-pf-type="DividerIcon2" class="sc-EgOky hhhGUX pf-239_"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 512 512"><path d="M453.3 19.3l39.4 39.4c25 25 25 65.5 0 90.5l-52.1 52.1 0 0-1-1 0 0-16-16-96-96-17-17 52.1-52.1c25-25 65.5-25 90.5 0zM241 114.9c-9.4-9.4-24.6-9.4-33.9 0L105 217c-9.4 9.4-24.6 9.4-33.9 0s-9.4-24.6 0-33.9L173.1 81c28.1-28.1 73.7-28.1 101.8 0L288 94.1l17 17 96 96 16 16 1 1-17 17L229.5 412.5c-48 48-109.2 80.8-175.8 94.1l-25 5c-7.9 1.6-16-.9-21.7-6.6s-8.1-13.8-6.6-21.7l5-25c13.3-66.6 46.1-127.8 94.1-175.8L254.1 128 241 114.9z"></path></svg></span></div><p class="sc-dQEsWe kFLVLU pf-242_ pf-text-1 pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fFlofg cnCjdX pf-244_"><strong>Authors &amp;&nbsp;Researchers<br>

